{"by": "DiogenesKynikos", "id": 43182314, "kids": [43188640, 43184062], "parent": 43182004, "text": "Luckily, the bottom rung of the distance ladder, parallax, is only dependent on geometry, and is therefore completely solid. With the Gaia space telescope, there are now parallax measurements almost to the center of the Milky Way.<p>Having parallax measurements to that distance helps to build multiple versions of the next rung in the ladder (such as Cepheids and the tip of the red giant branch).", "time": 1740563715, "type": "comment"}